            {
                "s2_paper_id": "0392a70fb323a875a0b3c19c804f65bd3778abad",
                "title": "Validation of an Enzyme\u2010Linked Immunosorbent Assay for Measuring Leptin, a Key Metabolic Hormone, in Dried Blood Spot Samples",
                "year": 2025,
                "venue": "American Journal of Human Biology",
                "citation_count": 0,
                "reference_count": 11,
                "abstract": "Leptin is an established biomarker of appetite regulation and energy status. Problematically, heavy reliance on invasive venipuncture sampling has limited leptin research with diverse human populations and groups such as children. Key questions remain about leptin's evolution and biological roles across the full range of humans. Here, we present and validate a new minimally invasive approach for measuring leptin in finger\u2010prick dried blood spots (DBS) using a commercial ELISA kit.",
